<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-240-704  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 240 704.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  April 27 1989 n1161 p1(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hackers blamed for Bristol shutdown. (Bristol and West BuildingSociety)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bicknell, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The IBM mainframe computer system network at Bristol and WestBuilding Society was down for most of a week in Apr 1989.andP;  Thereis speculation that the system shut itself down in order toprevent access by a persistent hacker.andP;  Bristol and West blamesthe crash on a fault in the system repaired by IBM engineerscalled in to investigate, but earlier in the week a hacker hadbeen attempting to break into the system.andP;  Normally a system shutsdown specific lines to secure itself after several failed accessattempts, but an entire system shutting down for that purpose isunusual.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Mainframe ComputersComputer CrimesComputer HackersSystem CrashSecurity Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>